title.narrative: Ending Tuberculosis in Lao PDR

description.narrative: Lao (Peoples Democratic Republic) - Tuberculosis - Ministry of Health of the Lao People's Democratic Republic - MOH. This program has the following goals: To reduce the burden of tuberculosis in Lao PDR and to reach the targets of the WHO END TB strategy. The objectives of this program are: Achieve universal and equitable access to TB diagnosis and treatment for all people suffering from TB. Manage drug resistant tuberculosis. Strengthen TB/HIV collaborative activities. Streamline the management of TB program in resilient and sustainable system for health (RSSH)
